    <p>Great Britain is divided into 8 traffic areas. Each area has a Traffic Commissioner whoâ€™s responsible for issuing
        licences. Northern Ireland has a separate system.</p>
    <p>Your operating licence needs to be valid for the area(s) in which your operating centre(s) are based. If you have
        operating centres in more than one traffic area, you will need a separate licence for each area.</p>
    <p>For Standard International licences where only Light goods vehicles are authorised, your operating licence needs
        to be valid for the area in which your address of establishment is based. If you have an address of
        establishment in more than one traffic area, you will need a separate licence for each area.</p>
